<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 1:24AM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT NORTHEASTERN SOMERSET AND SOUTH
CENTRAL CAMBRIA COUNTIES THROUGH 200 AM EDT...
At 124 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Ebensburg to near Windber. Movement was east at
30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Somerset, Windber, Ebensburg, Portage, Geistown, Berlin, Cresson,
Gallitzin, Friedens, Loretto, Salix-Beauty Line Park, Central City,
Beaverdale-Lloydell, Paint, Lilly, South Fork, Scalp Level,
Sankertown, Sidman and St. Michael.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
